en_1705917_0	Sicille Kotelawala, wife of former chairman of Ceylinco Group of Companies Lalith Kotelawala was detained by the Immigration and Emigration Officials on Thursday, February 4.
en_1705917_1	According to Police Media Spokesperson ASP Ruwan Gunasekera, she was later handed over to the Criminal Investigations Department.
en_1705917_2	Immigration and Emigration Controller, M.M. Ranasinghe stated that Sicille Kotelawala was detained upon her arrival at the Bandaranaike International Airport.
en_1705917_3	He noted that Sicille Kotelawala was detained when she returned to Sri Lanka from London.
